
Clone the repo and cd into the project folder:

git clone https://github.com/pydisandeep/minimalRAG.git
cd minimalRAG


Install dependencies:

Backend (Python)
cd backend
python -m venv venv   # create virtual environment (optional)


Activate venv (depending on your shell):

Windows CMD

venv\Scripts\activate


Windows PowerShell

venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1


Git Bash / Linux / macOS

source venv/bin/activate


Then install requirements:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Frontend (React)
cd ../frontend
npm install

üõ†Ô∏è Setup

üîë Hugging Face API Token Setup

This project requires a Hugging Face API token for model access.

Go to Hugging Face Tokens Page
https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens

Create a new Access Token (with at least ‚ÄúRead‚Äù permissions). or use existing token

Set it as an environment variable before running the backend:

Windows CMD

set HF_API_TOKEN=your_token_here


Windows PowerShell

$env:HF_API_TOKEN="your_token_here"


Linux / macOS / Git Bash

export HF_API_TOKEN=your_token_here




‚ñ∂Ô∏è Run with FastAPI + React (UI Mode)

üëâ Open two terminals: one for backend, one for frontend.

Backend

From the backend folder, activate your venv (as above), then run:

Windows (CMD / PowerShell):

python -m uvicorn app.fastapi:app --reload


Linux / macOS / Git Bash:

uvicorn app.fastapi:app --reload

Frontend

From the frontend folder, run:

npm start

‚ñ∂Ô∏è Run in CLI Mode (Optional)

If you don‚Äôt want UI/API, you can run a simple chatbot directly in the terminal.

Windows (CMD/PowerShell):

cd backend
python app\minimal_rag.py


Git Bash / Linux / macOS:

cd backend
python app/minimal_rag.py
